MOEX Sandbox Trading Bot - Step-by-Step Pipeline Description
===========================================================

This document provides a full, detailed, step-by-step description of what was implemented in this project so far, including architecture, data pipelines, modeling, evaluation, monitoring, and reporting.

------------------------------------------------------------
0) PROJECT MISSION AND OPERATING PRINCIPLES
------------------------------------------------------------

Primary objective:
- Build a modular algorithmic trading sandbox platform for MOEX equities.
- Start in T-Invest sandbox and dry-run mode.
- Use deterministic, incremental implementation suitable for Cursor context limits.
- Keep model logic, orchestration, risk, execution, and broker integrations separated.

Key principles enforced throughout implementation:
- Sandbox-first defaults and safety flags.
- No hardcoded secrets.
- Explicit stage-based pipeline.
- Reproducible artifacts and reports.
- Chronology-preserving, leakage-aware data processing.
- Standardized prediction output schema across model families.
- MLflow-first experiment tracking.
- Observability via Prometheus/Grafana and alerting skeleton via Telegram.


