11) MAIN OUTPUT ARTIFACT FLOW
------------------------------------------------------------

Data flow overview:
1) Market download:
   data/raw/market/*
2) Market preprocess:
   data/interim/market/*
3) News download:
   data/raw/news/items.jsonl
4) News preprocess:
   data/interim/news/items.jsonl
5) News mapping:
   data/processed/news/mapped_news.parquet
6) News features:
   data/processed/news/features/news_features.parquet
7) Market features:
   data/processed/market/features/market_features.parquet
8) Merge/split:
   data/processed/merged/train.parquet
   data/processed/merged/validation.parquet
   data/processed/merged/test.parquet
9) Model training outputs:
   models/base/*
   models/news/*
   models/ensemble/*
10) Evaluation and backtest:
   reports/*.json / reports/*.md
   artifacts/backtests/*
11) Comparison/promotion/publish/final:
   artifacts/comparison/*
   models/registry/*
   artifacts/published/*
   reports/final/*


------------------------------------------------------------
12) KNOWN LIMITS / NEXT ENGINEERING TARGETS
------------------------------------------------------------

Current implementation is intentionally MVP-oriented and interface-first in several areas:
- No RL.
- No live broker execution.
- No transformer NLP.
- No full orchestrated run_retrain_pipeline stage yet.
- Backtesting remains single-asset first with simplified execution model.
- Monitoring gauges are currently refreshed from local artifacts/reports.

Recommended next targets:
- full pipeline DAG runner for run_retrain_pipeline
- richer benchmark and walk-forward fold reports
- stricter schema versioning and data contracts
- fuller alertmanager + notifier integration loop
- model registry promotion policy hardening
- integration tests for complete end-to-end retrain cycle.

